When building a web application for the Java Enterprise Edition, Servlet API and related Java EE APIs must be provided by the web container (Tomcat) in runtime.
with a full-blown Tomcat servlet, these dependencies will be provided at runtime but this does not happen when using an embedded Tomcat.

There are two solutions.

**Solution 1: (Not recommended)**

change the scope of Tomcat from provided to compiled (comment or remove provided) to include the classes in the classpath.

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-tomcat&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

**Solution 2:**
Configure your IDE to add the provided dependencies to the classpath.

[Intellij IDEA][1]: 

&gt; Run -&gt; Edit Configurations.. -&gt; Build and Run -&gt; Modify options -&gt;   
&gt; add dependencies with provided scope to classpath

  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/SVYYh.png

