After extensive benchmarking, we found that using `rm -rf` was multiple times faster than using `FileUtils.deleteDirectory`. 

Of course, if you have a small or simple directory, it won&#39;t matter but in our case we had multiple gigabytes and deeply nested sub directories where it would take over 10 minutes with `FileUtils.deleteDirectory` and only 1 minute with `rm -rf`.

