**Yes you can!** here is how to manage it using `DefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler`:

in your `Application` class and in `onCreate` method create a exception handler like this 

[if you don&#39;t have `Application` class, try to create it and register it in your manifest file or simply ask for help]:

    open class MyApplication : Application() {
    
        override fun onCreate() {
            super.onCreate()
    
            // Setup handler for uncaught exceptions
            Thread.setDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler { _: Thread, throwable: Throwable -&gt;
                handleUncaughtException(throwable)
            }
    
        }
    
    
        /**
         * This function will handle uncaught runtime exceptions
         *
         * @param throwable throwable exception object
         */
        private fun handleUncaughtException(throwable: Throwable) {
            throwable.printStackTrace()
            exitProcess(1)
